{
  "texts": [
    "Although unsupervised learning is possible and is a growing field in NLP, it is not widely accessible to smaller groups due to large data requirements and the need for computer power.",
    "Companies that have such resources, such as Google or OpenAI, use it to create pre-trained models.",
    "Pre-trained embeddings and models are trained on a large corpus in an unsupervised manner, then fine-tuned in a supervised manner.",
    "36 These are then made available for other users, so that they can be used to support other supervised and semi-supervised learning projects, skipping some stages in collection and preprocessing.",
    "This may result in a small number of dominant players in language modelling."
  ]
}